summary: An immutable command. A command is a specific action or a set of actions that a user or an application requests the underlying system to perform. It can be a simple action such as invoking a system method or an OS command or representing a complex operation that calls a set of protected APIs over the internal or external network. A command can virtually do anything in the context of your application or service.
